==English==

===Etymology===
From Modified Latin ''Americanus'' (''America'' from Latinized name of  ''Amerigo'' Vespucci, Italian navigator of 1512).

===Pronunciation===
* US: {{SAMPA|/@"mEr@k@n/}}, {{IPA|/əˈmɛɹɪkən/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A person born in, or a [[citizen]] of, the [[United States of America]].
# An [[inhabitant]] of the [[America]]s. More often this is specified as either ''North American'', ''Central American'' or ''South American.''
# The English language as spoken in the USA; [[American English]].
#* '''1942''', We sat down in the central square and drank coffee and a man came up and spoke to us in '''American'''. — Rebecca West, ''Black Lamb and Grey Falcon'' (Canongate 2006, p. 756)

